@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Privacy Policy";
}

<section class="policy-page">
    <header class="policy-header">
        <p class="policy-kicker">Trust &amp; Stewardship</p>
        <h1>@ViewData["Title"]</h1>
        <p>
            EventEase values discretion. This policy explains what we collect, why we collect it, and how we protect your information
            while delivering venue, event, and booking management services.
        </p>
    </header>

    <div class="policy-sections">
        <section>
            <h2>1. Information We Collect</h2>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Account and profile details:</strong> such as names and contact information you provide in forms.</li>
                <li><strong>Event operations data:</strong> venue records, event details, booking schedules, and related metadata.</li>
                <li><strong>Technical data:</strong> browser type, device information, and usage patterns used to improve performance.</li>
            </ul>
        </section>

        <section>
            <h2>2. How We Use Information</h2>
            <ul>
                <li>To provide core scheduling, event coordination, and booking management features.</li>
                <li>To maintain service quality, secure operations, and troubleshoot technical issues.</li>
                <li>To improve design, accessibility, and performance across mobile and desktop experiences.</li>
            </ul>
        </section>

        <section>
            <h2>3. Data Protection &amp; Retention</h2>
            <p>
                We use layered safeguards to protect your data from unauthorized access, alteration, or disclosure. Records are retained
                only for as long as needed to support legitimate business and legal obligations.
            </p>
        </section>

        <section>
            <h2>4. Your Rights</h2>
            <p>
                You may request access, correction, or deletion of personal information where applicable by law. You may also request
                details about how your data has been used within the platform.
            </p>
        </section>

        <section>
            <h2>5. Cookies &amp; Essential Technologies</h2>
            <p>
                EventEase may use essential cookies or local storage to preserve session continuity, enhance navigation, and support secure
                interactions. These technologies are used responsibly and with respect for user privacy.
            </p>
        </section>

        <section>
            <h2>6. Policy Updates</h2>
            <p>
                We may update this policy to reflect service improvements or legal requirements. Material changes will be communicated
                through the website with an updated effective date.
            </p>
            <p class="effective-date"><strong>Effective Date:</strong> February 27, 2026</p>
        </section>
    </div>
</section>
